f Kali yuga, rational minds wouldn&#39;t accept anything that didn&#39;t =\r\n&quot;make sense&quot;. Being established in Self became an unnatural, ridiculous and=\r\n incomprehensible notion. So the &quot;spirit of comprehension&quot; (Mercury) became=\r\n relevant. An avatara corresponding to Mercury occurred and tried to explai=\r\nn being established in Self as a comprehensible notion, so that rational mi=\r\nnds of that age would accept it to an extent and attempt it.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;=\r\n &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Avataras occur based on the needs of collective consciousness. Of cour=\r\nse, if one&#39;s consciousness is in a different state from the collective cons=\r\nciousness of that time, the current avatara may not be relevant to one.\n&gt; &gt;=\r\n&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; I respect Rama, but I=\r\n\n&gt;  worship Krshna.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;I am\n&gt;  awestruck by Krishna and wor=\r\nship him, but I see Rama as an ideal that I MAY be able to emulate oneday. =\r\nIn fact, I recommend the approach to others.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Though I sa=\r\nid Rama and Krishna are almost the same, there is a difference between soul=\r\n and perfected mind. Soul is a spark of Shiva and a perfected mind is a spa=\r\nrk of Chit Shakti (whereas an imperfect mind is a spark of Maya shakti).\n&gt; =\r\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Best regards, Narasimha -------- Astrology & Spirit=\r\nuality Resources: http://www.vedicastrologer.org/\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;--------\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=\r\n=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;From: rajarshi nandy &lt;rajarshi14@...&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;To: &quot;vedic-wisdom@ya=\r\nhoogroups.com&quot; &lt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&gt; \n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;