 compares forms of Lor=\r\nd to clouds in sky and dirt in air. Just as sky *contains* clouds and is be=\r\nyond them, similarly Lord *contains* forms and is beyond them. So, again, w=\r\nhat is the meaning of a specific form that descended on earth being &quot;Lord H=\r\nimself&quot;? I am afraid people may be misinterpreting this notion based on the=\r\nir fancies and conditioning..\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;All beings are made up o=\r\nf paramatma (supreme/absolute being) and jivatma (living/relative being). T=\r\nhe latter portion is dominant in us and is responsible for desires and rebi=\r\nrth. Great avataras descend from a higher portion of paramatma. Very rarely=\r\n avataras descend entirely from paramatma without ANY jivatma portion. Rama=\r\n and Krishna are specific examples given by Parasara.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=\r\nThey are entirely divine, but they do not encapsulate the entire divinity!!=\r\n!!\n&gt;  After all, &quot;entire\n&gt;  divinity&quot; cannot be encapsulated by any form ju=\r\nst as no cloud can contain the entire sky. They take part in the drama obey=\r\ning and executing the divine will but NOT altering it. This applies to Kris=\r\nhna as well as Rama.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; =\r\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Buddha was great spiritual force in this world. But I do not\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=\r\n&gt; see him fit in the scheme of evolutionary Avatars. His\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; realizati=\r\non, the one he advocated, is a static realization,\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; an end in a voi=\r\nd.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;First, he IS mentioned in SB list of avataras as we=\r\nll as Parasara&#39;s list. If he does not &quot;fit&quot; in your &quot;scheme of evolutionary=\r\n Avatars&quot;, then your concept is possibly wrong and avataras are perhaps not=\r\n &quot;evolutionary&quot; as you theorize.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Secondly, as per Para=\r\nsara, Buddha corresponds to Mercury, who personifies logical mind and the s=\r\npirit of\n&gt;  investigation and comprehension. Logical mind\n&gt;  and its spirit=\r\n of comprehension are inherently fallible. Even a perfected spirit of compr=\r\nehension is not capable of grasping the Absolute Reality completely, for it=\r\n is beyond comprehension. So, no wonder it simplifies the Incomprehensible =\r\nin an attempt to comprehend! That is what Buddha ended up doing. However, l=\r\nogical mind has a great appeal in the Age of Reason in this Kali yuga. No w=\r\nonder Buddha was/is/will be a great spiritual force in this world in this a=\r\nge.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;If you dismi=\r\nss Parasara&#39;s linking of planets to avataras as a possible corruption, are =\r\nyou absolutely sure that the verses of SB you are relying on are perfect? (=\r\nIn any case, it&#39;s a different matter that you are only taking some SB verse=\r\ns and ignoring\n&gt;  some as\n&gt;  I\n&gt;  showed!.)\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;The bottom=\r\nline as far as I am concerned is that Pararsara&#39;s list actually makes amazi=\r\nngly coherent esoteric sense. The nature of each aspect of consciousness (e=\r\n.g. Buddha - spirit of comprehension, Saturn - spirit of patience & persist=\r\nence, Venus - spirit of happiness etc) and the story of corresponding avata=\r\nra DOES have a highly meaningful connection, esoterically speaking. After a=\r\nll, esoterically is how you really need to understand any higher scriptures=\r\n and notions in them.\n&gt; &gt;